Diagnosis.
This new genus can be easily recognized by several features unusual or unique among New World Exosternini. The single v-shaped annulus of the antennal club (
Fig. 1
) and the transversely incised prosternal keel (
Fig. 2
) are unique in Exosternini. The recurved and angulate frontal stria (
Figs. 5–6
), the truncate base of the prosternal keel (
Figs. 7–8
), the apically truncate prosternal lobe (
Figs. 7–8
), and the weakly bifidly toothed left mandible (
Figs. 5–6
) are found in few other New World Exosternini, and never in combination.
